---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const tabs = [
	{ id: 'software', label: 'software' },
	{ id: 'podcasts', label: 'podcasts' },
	{ id: 'blogs', label: 'blogs' },
	{ id: 'webpages', label: 'web pages' },
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`favorites — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="Software, podcasts, and blogs Drew actually uses and recommends."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article class="prose">
				<h1>My Favorite Things</h1>

				<p>
					This is a collection of my favorite tools, blogs, web pages, and podcasts =)
				</p>

				<div class="tabs" data-tabs>
					<div class="tablist" role="tablist" aria-label="Favorite things">
						{
							tabs.map((tab, i) => (
								<button
									role="tab"
									id={`tab-${tab.id}`}
									aria-controls={`panel-${tab.id}`}
									aria-selected={i === 0 ? 'true' : 'false'}
									tabindex={i === 0 ? undefined : -1}
								>
									{tab.label}
								</button>
							))
						}
					</div>

					<section
						class="panel"
						id="panel-software"
						role="tabpanel"
						aria-labelledby="tab-software"
					>
						<h2>Software</h2>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/gifox.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a href="https://gifox.app" rel="noopener">gifox</a>
							</h3>
							<p>
								Super easy and quick screen recorder that lets you create
								and edit gifs. Your PR reviewers will love you. I paid $15
								for a lifetime license. Amazing product.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/cleanshot.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a href="https://cleanshot.com" rel="noopener">CleanShot X</a>
							</h3>
							<p>
								This is just a great screen recording tool. I loved Loom prior to
								its acquisition by Atlassian, and I've tried to love Cap.so. But
								I've landed on cleanshot as the best tool for reliably recording demos.
								You might not need both gifox and cleanshot, but I bought the gifox
								lifetime license before I found cleanshot ¯\_(ツ)_/¯  
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/tableplus.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a href="https://tableplus.com" rel="noopener">TablePlus</a>
							</h3>
							<p>
								If you're a developer, you need a first-rate db client, and I actually
								picked up TablePlus after Kao at Coverbase recommended it. It's a lovely
								client, and I've tried a lot of them over the years.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/meetingbar.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a href="https://meetingbar.app" rel="noopener">MeetingBar</a>
							</h3>
							<p>
								This app sits in your Mac OS menu bar and does 2 critical
								things:
							</p>
							<ol>
								<li>Tells you when your next meeting is</li>
								<li>Lets you join that meeting with 2 clicks</li>
							</ol>
							<p>
								I support this app through Patreon. It's made in Ukraine.
								What more do you need to know?
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/runjs.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a href="https://runjs.app" rel="noopener">RunJS</a>
							</h3>
							<p>
								Just a nice standalone JavaScript repl. You can install
								packages. I find it real handy when I need to remember just
								how weird JavaScript is and want tight feedback loops.
							</p>
						</div>
					</section>

					<section
						class="panel"
						id="panel-podcasts"
						role="tabpanel"
						aria-labelledby="tab-podcasts"
					>
						<h2>Podcasts</h2>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/soft-skills.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a href="https://softskills.audio" rel="noopener"
									>Soft Skills Engineering</a
								> <span class="byline">by Jamison Dance and Dave Smith</span>
							</h3>
							<p>
								This is one of my favorite podcasts; Dave and Jamison are
								fun to listen to and they often have great advice for
								navigating the non-technical aspects of building software
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/in-depth.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a href="https://review.firstround.com/podcast/" rel="noopener"
									>In Depth</a
								> <span class="byline">by First Round Review</span>
							</h3>
							<p>
								they interview folks who have worked in various roles at
								successful startups, and the conversations are always
								illuminating. I've quoted them elsewhere on my blog!
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/joy-of-why.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a
									href="https://www.quantamagazine.org/tag/the-joy-of-why/"
									rel="noopener">The Joy of Why</a
								> <span class="byline">by Quanta Magazine</span>
							</h3>
							<p>
								they explore really fascinating and difficult subjects, and
								Steven and Janna are both excellent interviewers. My
								favorite episodes include the ones on graph theory, dark
								matter, string theory (which I previously found utterly
								inaccessible), and knots.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/switchblade-sisters.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a
									href="https://maximumfun.org/podcasts/switchblade-sisters/"
									rel="noopener">Switchblade Sisters</a
								> <span class="byline">by April Wolfe</span>
							</h3>
							<p>
								April is, IMO, the greatest podcast interviewer of all
								time. She is so prepared and knowledgeable, and she brings
								out the unique qualities and experience of each of her
								guests. Each episode is a very tight 45 minutes of insider
								baseball on the guest's favorite genre film — and the guest
								must be either an actor, writer, or director.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/lets-appreciate.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a href="https://kylascanlon.com" rel="noopener"
									>Let's Appreciate</a
								> <span class="byline">by Kyla Scanlon</span>
							</h3>
							<p>
								Kyla writes poetry about the economy and coined the term
								"vibe-cession". Anything she publishes is going to be her
								best work and well-worthy of your time. It's the rare
								podcast where I have to listen at a playback rate less
								than 1.
							</p>
						</div>
					</section>

					<section
						class="panel"
						id="panel-blogs"
						role="tabpanel"
						aria-labelledby="tab-blogs"
					>
						<h2>Blogs I like</h2>

						<ul class="blogroll">
							<li>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/jvns.png"
									alt=""
									width="20"
									height="20"
								/>
								<a href="https://jvns.ca" rel="noopener">Julia Evans</a>
							</li>
							<li>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/chelsea-troy.png"
									alt=""
									width="20"
									height="20"
								/>
								<a href="https://chelseatroy.com" rel="noopener"
									>Chelsea Troy</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/lethain.png"
									alt=""
									width="20"
									height="20"
								/>
								<a href="https://lethain.com" rel="noopener"
									>irrational exuberance</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/charity-wtf.png"
									alt=""
									width="20"
									height="20"
								/>
								<a
									href="https://charity.wtf/author/mipsytipsy/"
									rel="noopener">Charity Majors</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/elided-branches.png"
									alt=""
									width="20"
									height="20"
								/>
								<a href="https://www.elidedbranches.com" rel="noopener"
									>Elided Branches</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<span class="glyph" aria-hidden="true">//</span>
								<a
									href="https://litonico.github.io/about-computers/"
									rel="noopener">About Computers by Lito Nicolai</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/computers-and-people.png"
									alt=""
									width="20"
									height="20"
								/>
								<a href="https://computersandpeople.com" rel="noopener"
									>computers and people</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/dannorth.png"
									alt=""
									width="20"
									height="20"
								/>
								<a href="https://dannorth.net/blog" rel="noopener"
									>Dan North</a
								>
							</li>
							<li>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/fromjason.png"
									alt=""
									width="20"
									height="20"
								/>
								<span>
									<a
										href="https://www.fromjason.xyz/p/notebook/where-have-all-the-websites-gone/"
										rel="noopener">Where have all the websites gone?</a
									> by Jason Velazquez
								</span>
							</li>
							<li>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/zach-holman.png"
									alt=""
									width="20"
									height="20"
								/>
								<span>
									<a href="https://zachholman.com/about" rel="noopener"
										>Zach Holman</a
									> (especially <a
										href="https://zachholman.com/talk/utc-is-enough-for-everyone-right"
										rel="noopener">UTC is enough for everyone… right?</a
									>)
								</span>
							</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section
						class="panel"
						id="panel-webpages"
						role="tabpanel"
						aria-labelledby="tab-webpages"
					>
						<h2>Web pages</h2>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/wikipedia.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a
									href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_in_Indiana"
									rel="noopener">Time in Indiana</a
								> <span class="byline">on Wikipedia</span>
							</h3>
							<p>
								There's a perennial debate about eliminating daylight savings time,
								and I learned from deep, personal experience that timezones are so
								much more complicated and political than you think they are. This
								wikipedia page is an excellent companion to Zach Holman's blog post.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="entry">
							<h3>
								<img
									src="/images/favorites/wikipedia.png"
									alt=""
									width="28"
									height="28"
								/>
								<a
									href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anywhere_on_Earth"
									rel="noopener">Anywhere on Earth</a
								> <span class="byline">on Wikipedia</span>
							</h3>
							<p>
								There's a last place on Earth where any given day is still
								going — Howland and Baker Islands, out in the Pacific at
								UTC−12. "Anywhere on Earth" is the convention built on that: a
								deadline isn't blown until the date is gone everywhere, which
								lands at noon UTC the next day.
							</p>
						</div>
					</section>
				</div>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />

		<script>
			const container = document.querySelector('[data-tabs]');
			if (container) {
				const tabs = [...container.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[role="tab"]')];
				const panels = [...container.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[role="tabpanel"]')];

				function select(tab: HTMLButtonElement, focus = true) {
					for (const t of tabs) {
						const active = t === tab;
						t.setAttribute('aria-selected', String(active));
						t.tabIndex = active ? 0 : -1;
					}
					for (const p of panels) {
						p.hidden = p.id !== tab.getAttribute('aria-controls');
					}
					if (focus) tab.focus();
					history.replaceState(
						null,
						'',
						'#' + tab.id.replace('tab-', ''),
					);
				}

				tabs.forEach((tab, i) => {
					tab.addEventListener('click', () => select(tab, false));
					tab.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
						const delta =
							e.key === 'ArrowRight' ? 1 : e.key === 'ArrowLeft' ? -1 : 0;
						if (delta) {
							e.preventDefault();
							select(tabs[(i + delta + tabs.length) % tabs.length]);
						}
					});
				});

				// panels start visible so the page works without JS;
				// switching to tab mode hides all but the selected one
				container.classList.add('tabs-ready');
				const fromHash = tabs.find(
					(t) => t.id === 'tab-' + location.hash.slice(1),
				);
				select(fromHash ?? tabs[0], false);
			}
		</script>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.prose {
		max-width: 62ch;
	}

	.tablist {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		margin: 2rem 0;
	}
	.tablist button {
		font-family: 'Space Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		padding: 0.5em 1.1em;
		min-height: 44px;
		color: var(--ink);
		background-color: var(--paper-deep);
		border: 2px solid var(--rule);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-offset) var(--shadow-offset) 0 var(--rule);
		cursor: pointer;
	}
	.tablist button:hover {
		background-color: var(--acid);
		color: var(--acid-ink);
	}
	.tablist button[aria-selected='true'] {
		background-color: var(--acid);
		color: var(--acid-ink);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-offset-pressed) var(--shadow-offset-pressed) 0
			var(--rule);
		transform: translate(
			calc(var(--shadow-offset) - var(--shadow-offset-pressed)),
			calc(var(--shadow-offset) - var(--shadow-offset-pressed))
		);
	}

	/* tab labels replace the section headings once JS takes over */
	.tabs-ready .panel > h2 {
		position: absolute !important;
		height: 1px;
		width: 1px;
		overflow: hidden;
		clip-path: inset(50%);
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.entry {
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	.entry h3 {
		margin-bottom: 0.4em;
	}
	.entry img,
	.blogroll img {
		border: 2px solid var(--rule);
		box-shadow: none;
		background-color: #fff;
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}
	.entry img {
		display: inline-block;
		width: 28px;
		height: 28px;
		vertical-align: -0.3em;
		margin-right: 0.35rem;
	}
	.byline {
		font-family: 'Atkinson', Georgia, serif;
		font-weight: 400;
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: var(--ink-soft);
	}

	.blogroll {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
	}
	.blogroll li {
		display: flex;
		align-items: baseline;
		gap: 0.6rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.75em;
	}
	.blogroll img,
	.blogroll .glyph {
		width: 20px;
		height: 20px;
		align-self: center;
	}
	.blogroll .glyph {
		font-family: 'Space Mono', ui-monospace, monospace;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 0.65rem;
		line-height: 16px;
		text-align: center;
		color: var(--ink);
		border: 2px solid var(--rule);
		background-color: var(--paper-deep);
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	.porter-note {
		margin-top: 2.5rem;
		padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
		border: 2px solid var(--rule);
		background-color: var(--paper-deep);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}
	.porter-note p {
		margin: 0;
	}
</style>
